<title>HONG KONG: Wartime Chinese guerrillas join HK handover gala.</title>
<headline>Wartime Chinese guerrillas join HK handover gala.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-06-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Former Chinese guerrillas who fought against the occupying Japanese army in Hong Kong in World War Two arrived to celebrate the British colony's reversion to China, a newspaper said on Monday.</p>
<p>A group of 101 guerrillas came from southern China's Guangzhou city on Sunday to join festivities marking Hong Kong's return to Chinese rule at midnight on Monday, the pro-Beijing Wen Wei Po reported.</p>
<p>Hong Kong was occupied by the Japanese military for three years and eight months before the end of World War Two.</p>
